text.section:
In this section, "public employer" means:
a unit;
a county;
a municipality in the State;
a school district in the State; or
any special district in the State.

section.section:
A public employer may buy, furnish, or require an employee to purchase or acquire an item listed in paragraph (1) of this subsection that is manufactured outside of the United States, if:
the item or a similar item is not manufactured or available for purchase in the United States;
the item or a similar item is not manufactured or available for purchase in the United States in reasonably available quantities;
the price of the item or a similar item manufactured in the United States exceeds the price of a similar, available item that is not manufactured in the United States by an unreasonable amount; or
the quality of the item or a similar item manufactured in the United States is substantially less than the quality of a comparably priced, similar, and available item that is not manufactured in the United States.
